SPOOFY got bumped between foes at the start and conceded two lengths to the leader, chased along the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, cut the corner into upper stretch and trailed.

THREE ZERO showed good speed, set a joint pace on the outside of a foe while loosely between horses, vied in the three then two path on the turn, came under a drive in upper stretch, battled on even terms for the lead into the final sixteenth but was out-kicked and missed the superfecta. WINTER SON raced just off the pace between rivals, went two then three wide on the turn, chased under a drive into the final furlong and also lacked the needed response. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY MISCHIEVOUS six paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five wide for home, rallied to take command just outside the eighth pole outside a pair, dug in gamely to fend off the runner up and prevail by a head at the finish. DORTH VADER chased four paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking inside into the turn, tipped out to the two path at the five-sixteenths, swung three to four wide for home, was loosely between foes with three-sixteenths to go, dug in and fought on to the finish in game fashion but was ultimately denied at the end. OCCULT steadied at the start when MUNNYS GOLD came inwards, chased four to five wide down the backstretch trading lanes with FROSTY O TOOLE in a private spat separate from the rest of the field, tucked just off the inside through the turn, went five wide into upper stretch and offered up a mild kick closing belatedly outside. MUNNYS GOLD broke in at the start forcing OCCULT to steady off her heels, showed the way in hand five paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn while under some pressure from a pair, continued just off the inside for home under threat from a pair of rivals, got collared near the eighth pole and weakened in the late stages. ACCEDE broke in at the start bumping GOODGIRL BADHABITS, chased six paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn, took the inside route into upper stretch and weakened. RANDOMIZED chased five wide down the backstretch and then three wide through the turn, went six wide for home and weakened. FROSTY O TOOLE chased four then three wide trading lanes briefly down the backstretch with OCCULT, came under coaxing with seven-sixteenths remaining, went five to six wide for home, made no impact. GOODGIRL BADHABITS stumbled at the start and was bumped by ACCEDE, chased seven paths off the inside down the backstretch and then three wide through the turn, went two to three wide into upper stretch and folded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Belmont Gold Cup S. - Grade2 BELMONT PARK RACE 10 2M Turf CR: 111. Stakes Purse 250000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SISKANY (GB) was reserved under a hold while inside to the two path, moved closer in the three path on the final turn, made a four wide bid at the quarter-pole then took the lead in upper stretch, fought outside of a foe into the final furlong, shook clear near the sixteenth-pole and proved best under strong urging. THE GREY WIZARD (IRE) angled in early, was reserved near the back on the outside while three to four wide, moved closer on the final turn, chased under a drive in the stretch and just got up for the place. BRITISH ROYALTY settled on the inside, hugged the hedge while reserved off the pace, came under some urging on the final turn, squeezed through against the rail in the stretch and finished willingly to just miss the place while able to get the show. AMAZING GRACE (GER) was reserved on the inside, came under urging on the final turn, squeezed through to make a bid along the hedge into the stretch, battled with the winner under a drive until inside the furlong marker then was outfinished. CIBOLIAN was reserved towards the rear while two path to the inside, came under urging on the third turn and improved position. HIGH DEFINITION (IRE) was reserved on the outside, went four wide on the turns, was asked on the final bend, chased into the final furlong and came up empty. TIDE OF THE SEA went to the front, showed the way while two path to the inside, lost the lead near the seven-eighths then regained the advantage outside the five-eighths, was headed by the winner into upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and gave way. BARBADOS (IRE) was hard held while saving ground early, rounded the second turn in the two path, was reserved towards the back, went three then four wide on the final turn and failed to threaten. STRONG TIDE was reserved while two path to the inside, came under encouragement going around the final turn and also failed to rally. CHANNEL MAKER tracked the pace on the outside while two to three wide, was asked on the final turn, chased into the final furlong and weakened. TARTINI was reserved while in the three path, came under urging in the two path on the final turn and lacked the needed response. L'IMPERATOR (FR) was last to commence, tugged hard on the bit in the two path under a vigorous hold, moved out five wide midway through the second turn, rushed up on the outside to get the lead nearing the seven-eighths, lost the advantage outside the five-eighths, came up empty on the final turn and capitulated. CROSS BORDER settled towards the front on the outside while three to four wide, came up empty near the half-mile pole and faltered then was eased in the stretch but walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: POPPY FLOWER chased just off the inside from mid pack, remained on hold until set down angled out four to five wide into upper stretch, closed well outside to issue a challenge inside the final furlong and was just up in the last jump to the wire. BUBBLE ROCK established the front from the start and was under a firm hold three to four paths off the hedge down the backstretch through swift splits despite the rating, went three then two wide through the turn under wraps, took the inside route into upper stretch and had the field get busy when given a notch to work with near the eighth pole, got roused inside that station, dug in under a light drive and was nailed at the finish. AMY C (GB) three wide in pursuit, got let out spinning four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive running on willingly to secure the show honors. BAY STORM just off the inside in pursuit, tucked inside through the turn and remained on hold continuing in the inside route into upper stretch, got roused nearing the eighth pole and ran on to the finish. GOIN' GOOD four then three wide in pursuit, got set down spinning three wide into upper stretch, weakened in the late stages. CLITHEROE (GB) stumbled at the start and was bumped by SARAH HARPER, who broke outwards, then got forced to steady briefly conceding four lengths to the front, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, took the inside route into upper stretch, tipped to the two path straightened away, stayed on one paced to the finish but was outfinished. MESSIDOR (IRE) chased four wide under reserve until let out angled seven wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild bid, got outkicked to the finish. SARAH HARPER broke out at the start bumping CLITHEROE, who had just stumbled, chased three then two wide, got let out spinning three wide at the head of the stretch, weakened in the drive.
